Sass and spice and a whole bunch of nice is how ladybug is best described. She loves everyone and sets very clear boundaries with other dogs and kids.

Ladybug was found in bad shape on the mean streets of Texas. Luckily she went to the best foster in the world who has nursed her back to health. Ladybug is doing very well now although she still has some skin allergies. A high quality wholesome diet makes all the difference in the world. 

Ladybug is fostered in a home with multiple other dogs, a lot of personalities, and an 8 year old child. She gets along with all of them and looks forward to her time playing outside with them. She is crate trained, but at night she prefers to share a dog bed with the 8 year old child. 

Ladybug is currently being fostered in Houston, TX. We have adopted to many very happy families in your area and can provide references. We use an amazing ground transport that goes to the your area twice a month. 

Ladybug is up to date on shots, neutered, and microchipped. Please fill out an application on our website www.goodlif3bullyrescue.org/adoption-application-1 or email us at goodlif3adoptions@gmail.com if you are interested in Ladybug.

animal.description:
Sass and spice and a whole bunch of nice is how ladybug is best described. She loves everyone and sets very clear boundaries with other dogs and kids.

Ladybug was found in bad shape on the mean streets of Texas. Luckily she went to the best foster in the world who has nursed her back to health. Ladybug is doing very well now although she still has some skin allergies. A high quality wholesome diet makes all the difference in the world. 

Ladybug is fostered in a home with multiple other dogs, a lot of personalities, and an 8 year old child. She gets along with all of them and looks forward to her time playing outside with them. She is crate trained, but at night she prefers to share a dog bed with the 8 year old child. 

Ladybug is currently being fostered in Houston, TX. We have adopted to many very happy families in your area and can provide references. We use an amazing ground transport that goes to the your area twice a month. 

Ladybug is up to date on shots, neutered, and microchipped. Please fill out an application on our website www.goodlif3bullyrescue.org/adoption-application-1 or email us at goodlif3adoptions@gmail.com if you are interested in Ladybug.

animal.description:
To be considered for adopting a dog from Canine Lifeline, you must have an approved application must be on file. Please visit http://www.caninelifeline.org/adoption-process/ for more information about our adoption process and to submit an online application.

Cecelia is a loving and affectionate 1 year-old Boxer mix girl who came to us from an overcrowded county dog shelter. We don't have any history on her pre-shelter life or how she came to be at the shelter. Cecelia only weighs about 28 pounds so is definitely mixed with something smaller. For a young dog, she has a wonderfully calm and gentle demeanor. She has gotten along well with all other dogs she's met since coming to us but may prefer her canine buddies on the calm side. Cecelia also enjoys meeting new people and loves to snuggle up with her human friends once playtime is over. She has had excellent crate manners in her foster home so should be able to master the house rules fairly quickly in her new home. She walks quite nicely on a leash for a young dog and looks forward to accompanying her new family on lots of walks around her new neighborhood. Cecelia will likely need a sweater though as she's got a very short coat and doesn't seem to be a fan of cold weather. She would love a cozy spot by the fireplace to curl up and relax and we can't wait to see her doing just that in her new home. Cecelia weighs about 28 pounds and her adoption fee is $325. She's spayed, heartworm negative and on monthly preventative, up to date on vaccinations including bivalent canine influenza, wormed, on flea and tick preventative, and microchipped. As part of the adoption process, all adopters must commit to a two-week adjustment period to make sure it's a great match before the adoption is finalized. Please email info@caninelifeline.org if you're interested in Cecelia. An approved application is required before we schedule meets with any of our dogs. Please note that we don't place our dogs in homes with children under 7 years of age. We correspond via email so please check your junkmail or spam folder to make sure our reply hasn't landed in there. Please visit our website at www.caninelifeline.org to see more photos of Cecelia and to submit an online application if you live in Northeast OH.

animal.description:
Meet our newest MISFIT, a sweet senior named RUFUS. He has roughed it for most of his life and is looking for a loving home to spend his golden years in. We were told that he is around 12 years old, though we suspect he may be younger. RUFUS does well with other dogs and is equally happy to rough house with the puppies in his foster home as he is to snooze the day away on a dog bed with his fellow seniors. He is irresistibly sweet and goofy and near impossible not to love. He appears to have spent most of his life outdoors, though has adapted to indoor life well and is OK being crated when left home alone. We’ve had no problems with him in the house (no chewing, no marking) except for his regular attempts to sneak up onto the couch (lol). RUFUS still has plenty of spunk for an older dog and enjoys playing and going for walks.

If you’re interested in adopting RUFUS, please shoot us an email at misfitrescue@gmail.com and we’ll forward you our adoption questionnaire. His adoption fee is $75.00, which covers his neuter and basic vaccinations.

animal.description: Theona #7497 is a beautiful 6-year-old female, Mastiff mix. Theo is a well-adjusted friendly gal. She seems to love everyone she meets. She is good a meeting dogs. She is crate trained and knows the commands sit, down and come. She enjoys going on walks and pulls only when she has to go potty. Theo thinks she is a lap dog. She loves to ride in the car. She came to us with Ehrlichia  and we are seeking an adopter who will continue LCAR’s provided treatment at no cost.  She weighs 125 pounds and is full grown. This pup is microchipped. We believe you can always teach an ‘old’ dog new tricks, so we highly recommend continued obedience training for this smart pup; it stimulates the dog's mind and establishes a good dog/adopter relationship. This pup, like all pups, should be on heartworm preventative; an ounce of prevention is worth a pound of cure. If you are interested in adopting this dog, and are already approved to adopt through our organization, please contact dogs@lastchanceanimalrescue.org with the pup’s name and ID number in the subject line. OTHERWISE, please submit an adoption application online: http://www.lastchanceanimalrescue.org/adoptus.html E-mail dogs@lastchanceanimalrescue.org with questions. Stay tuned to our Facebook page for updates: www.facebook.com/LCARMD #adoptlove #PicMe #petsmartcharities

animal.description:
Meet gorgeous Lucero!

Lucero would do best in an adult home. She does not do well around toddlers or babies. We dont know what, if anything happened to her in her past, but she does not like young children.  She's living in foster home with a sweet, small boy dog and we'd love to see her in a forever home with a similar dog - a dog that will accept her and love her and bond with her (but it's not a deal breaker since she loves her people!).  Lucero is about 3-4 years old and around 8-pounds.  She's already spayed, healthy and had a dental. She's a very special little lady who loves her walks and LOVES to snuggle up.  Although she is as sweet as sugar, she is looking for an experienced home that knows how to implement boundaries and limitations - in return you'll get the sweetest, most adorable, portable  companion ever!  If you'd like to apply to adopt Lucero, submit our online adoption application on our website.

This is what her foster mom had to say about her:

Lucy is the sweetest little people-lover and belly-forward super snuggler. Her favorite thing is to be right up next to you on the couch. She is very observant and keeps a keen eye on what is happening around her. She likes calm & predictable environments. She's has an independent streak but will also shadow you all around the house. If her self-confidence is shaken she can experience separation anxiety, but when her confidence is built up, she's happy alone. She dances in circles when you come home. She loves to blanket-burrow and chew her yack and bully sticks inside an enclosed (cat?) bed. She's an expert at snatching soft toys tossed up in the air. She's a quick learner and only aims to be good. Lucy is an easy, delicate, sweetheart of a dog.
